<TITLE> Special food for fasting Khaleda, Hasina </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sept 14 (bdnews24.com)  Special foods or iftari has been arranged for former prime ministers Khaleda Zia and Sheikh Hasina now detained in the special jails housed in the Sangsad Bhaban complex. The menu for their iftar include gram, piaju , beguni , aloor chop , kofir chop , puffed rice, date, ripe papaya, apple, naspati , grapes, jilapi , juice and desserts ( payesh firni . "Both former prime ministers Khaleda Zia and Sheikh Hasina are fasting. They had shehri at night," deputy inspector general, prisons, Major Shamsul Haider Siddiqui told bdnews24.com Friday. "As they are VIP detainees special iftari have been arranged for them." Major Siddiqui said the two former prime ministers offered tarabi prayers after the Esha prayers Thursday night. Hasina was arrested from her Sudha Sadan home in Dhanmondi on July 16 and Khaleda Zia and her younger son Arafat Rahman Coco from their Shahid Mainul Road home in Dhaka Cantonment on Sept 3. Hasina and Khaleda were sent to special jails following court orders. Coco is now under treatment at the Coronary Care Unit (CCU) of Bangabandhu Sheikh Mujib Medical University Hospital. Khaleda's elder son Tarique Rahman has been detained in Dhaka Central Jail. bdnew
